com.cyc.kb

Interface KbCollection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    KbObject, KbObject.KbObjectWithArity, KbTerm
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FirstOrderCollection, SecondOrderCollection
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FirstOrderCollectionWrapper, KbCollectionWrapper, SecondOrderCollectionWrapper

    public interface KbCollection
extends KbTerm
    The top-level interface corresponding to Cyc #$Collection. A KbCollection is defined primarily by its specializations and generalizations in a multiple-inheritance subsumption hierarchy. Every KbTerm is an instance of at least one KbCollection.

      • addGeneralizationSentence

        Sentence addGeneralizationSentence(KbCollection moreGeneral)
                            throws KbTypeException,
                                   CreateException
        This method returns the Sentence (#$genls this moreGeneral). The key difference between this and addGeneralization(com.cyc.kb.KbCollection) is that, this method does not make any assertion in the KB. The sentence form of the assertion is generally useful when seeking user feedback before asserting into the KB. Use Sentence.assertIn(com.cyc.kb.Context) to assert the sentence in a Context.
        Parameters:
        moreGeneral - the generalization of this
        Returns:
        the #$genls sentence between this and moreGeneral
        Throws:
        KbTypeException
        CreateException

      • getInstances

        <O> Collection<? extends O> getInstances()
        Finds the asserted instances of this KbCollection from the default context specified by DefaultContext.forQuery(). For KbCollections that are instances of #$FirstOrderCollection, this can only return Individuals. For other collections, it can only return KbCollections or its subclasses.
        Type Parameters:
        O - the class the instances are cast to. Typically Individual or KbCollection.
        Returns:
        collection of objects of Type O

      • getInstances

        <O> Collection<O> getInstances(Context ctx)
        Finds the asserted instances of this KbCollection from a particular context. For KbCollections that are instances of #$FirstOrderCollection, this can only return Individuals. For other collections, it can only return KbCollections or its subclasses.

        Type Parameters:
        O - the class the instances are cast to Typically Individual or KbCollection.
        Parameters:
        ctx - the context of query
        Returns:
        objects of O

      • isGeneralizationOf

        boolean isGeneralizationOf(KbCollection moreSpecific,
                           Context ctx)
        Determine whether this KbCollection is a generalization of moreSpecific in some context. Essentially, this amounts to determining whether (#$genls moreSpecific this) is true. Note that (#$genls moreSpecific this) need not be asserted to be true.
        Parameters:
        moreSpecific - the possibly more specific collection
        ctx - the context where the fact is queried
        Returns:
        true if (#$genls moreSpecific this) is true
